5 F. Pursuant to the Inherent Rights clause in Section 2 of
6 Article II of the Oklahoma Constitution which states “All persons
7 have the inherent right to life, liberty, the pursuit of happiness,
8 and the enjoyment of the gains of their own industry”, during a
9 pandemic under a declared state of emergency by the Governor or the
10 President of the United States, the Governor of this state shall not
11 close or force the closing of any business without documented
12 scientific evidence that the nature of a particular business
13 actually contributes to the direct spreading of disease relating to
14 the pandemic. The Governor shall be required to give notice and
15 hearing to any business determined to be nonessential or detrimental
16 to the health and safety of citizens during a pandemic before
17 issuing an executive order against keeping such business open.
